# Verification & Honesty Standards

## Core Principle

**NEVER claim something works without verifying it actually works.**

---

## Verification Requirements

### ❌ NOT SUFFICIENT

Checking if code exists:
```tsx
// ❌ BAD: Assuming this works
grep "className.*card-glow-lux" components/ui/card.tsx
// Found! ✅ [CLAIMED: "Card shimmer working!"]
```

### ✅ REQUIRED

Verify the actual effect renders:
```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: Testing visual effect
1. Check class is applied
2. Check CSS utility exists in globals.css
3. Check CSS has required properties (overflow: hidden, position: relative)
4. Test in browser OR acknowledge "needs visual verification"
```

---

## Audit Standards

### When Auditing Components

**Required checks**:
1. ✅ Class is in component file
2. ✅ CSS utility exists in globals.css
3. ✅ CSS has ALL required properties for effect to work
4. ✅ No conflicting styles override it
5. ⚠️ **STATE UNCERTAINTY** if cannot test in browser

### Report Template

```markdown
## [Component] Audit

**Classes Applied**: [list]
**CSS Utilities Found**: [list]
**Required Properties**: [check each]
**Potential Conflicts**: [list any]
**Visual Testing**: ⚠️ NEEDS BROWSER TEST or ✅ VERIFIED

**Status**: 
- ✅ Code is correct
- ⚠️ Visual effect needs user confirmation
```

